<br>
Vulnerability is something that they have no resistance to damage from.  Effectiveness is their general effectiveness against attacks.  Special Protection covers the damage types that are not the same as their overall effectiveness or their vulnerabilities.<br>
<br>
Armor also contributes to a creature's resistance to damage, though I don't know if it affects vulnerabilities.  If something has light armor, and your weapon does not have light armor piercing or higher, not only will your damage will be halved but you will also have to deal with the resistance to that type of damage.<br>
<br>
I have no idea what ferocity does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=itossk>Itossk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#70DB93>(11/14/03 11:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Statistics</span><hr size=1> Curiouser and Curiouser ...   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alladdim>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#70DB93>(11/19/03 3:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Statistics</span><hr size=1> As with the deathblow stat ... <br>
<br>
Yes - The creature will automatically deathblows its opponent after incapacitation.<br>
<br>
No - The creature will not deathblow its opponent after incapacitation.<br>
<br>
What this means on pvp is that your pet will auto deathblow the player it is engaging if your pet deathblows. Otherwise it will simply return to your side after it incapacitates the target that it is engaging (another player).<br>
<br>
On PvE, if the creature incapacitates you while u're fighting it, it will kill you outright if it does deathblow. If not it will simply wander away after a while after it incapacitates you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=encymnon>Encymnon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#70DB93>(11/20/03 7:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=137.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet Statistics</span><hr size=1> But only if you havent put a DOT on it ... if you bleed or otherwise DOT a creature that doesnt Deathblow (PVE), it will remember you when you get back up after incapacitation, they will remember you.... <p>Bards - the &quot;clothing-optional&quot; class.<br>
